fuzzing_params.Constraints: date.length == 10, date[4] == date[7] == '-', and all other date[i]'s are digits. The input is generated such that date represents a valid Gregorian calendar date between Jan 1st, 1900 and Dec 31st, 2100 (both inclusive).

problem_info.title: 3280. Convert Date to Binary
test_examples: Example 1: Input: date = 2080-02-29 Output: 100000100000-10-11101 Explanation: 100000100000, 10, and 11101 are the binary representations of 2080, 02, and 29 respectively.
Example 2: Input: date = 1900-01-01 Output: 11101101100-1-1 Explanation: 11101101100, 1, and 1 are the binary representations of 1900, 1, and 1 respectively.
